#### .attr()
```javascript
    .attr(attr_name)
    .attr(attr_name, new_value)
    .attr(attr_name, function(index, old_value))
```

- Returns the attribute matching the attr_name for the first element in the set of selected elements. Returns undefined for attributes that have not been set.
- Sets the value of an attribute. New_value may be a String, Number, or Null (special case).
- Set the value of an attribute by defining a function to return a String value. The function receives the index of the selected element in the selected elements set and the old value of the attribute.

**Note:** Notes: To loop through attributes of multiple selected elements, use javascript .forEach or .map (or jQuery .each and .map).



